title: Historical Newspaper Articles, Volume 1
creator: Various
description: The first LibriVox collection of Historical Newspaper Articles. The LibriVox catalog page for this work lists the LibriVox readers and has links to the texts. Public Domain newspaper articles in the US span a period of nearly two and a half centuries. Subjects, styles, period, publisher, and length vary greatly. This collection is a sampling of twenty such articles including one from the Journal de Paris. Although some of the works on the Librivox catalog such as the Federalist Papers were published in newspapers, this is the first collection of newspaper articles. (Summary by James Smith). For more information on LibriVox, or to volunteer, please see: http://librivox.org/ Download M4B (59MB)
subject: librivox; news; history
